===Anime===
{{see also|List of Boruto: Naruto Next Generations episodes}}
At the ''Naruto'' and ''Boruto'' stage event at [[Jump Festa]] on 17 December 2016, it had been announced that the manga series would be adapted into an anime project,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-17/boruto-manga-gets-anime-project-in-april-2017/.110033|title=Boruto Manga Gets Anime Project in April 2017|date=17 December 2016|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=23 February 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20161217104955/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-17/boruto-manga-gets-anime-project-in-april-2017/.110033|archivedate=17 December 2016|df=}}</ref> which was later confirmed to be a television series adaptation that would feature an original story.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-17/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-reveals-promo-video-key-visual-returning-cast/.110036|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Anime Reveals Promo Video, Key Visual, Returning Cast (Updated)|date=17 December 2016|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=23 February 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221101818/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-17/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-reveals-promo-video-key-visual-returning-cast/.110036|archivedate=21 December 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-01-26/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-features-original-story/.111500|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Anime Features Original Story|date=26 January 2017|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=23 February 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170204053100/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-01-26/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-features-original-story/.111500|archivedate=4 February 2017|df=}}</ref> Additionally, an [[original video animation]] was previously released as a part of [[CyberConnect2]]'s [[video game]] collection, ''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm Trilogy'' (2017), which depicts a new mission where Boruto's team has to stop a thief.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/anime/2017/06/13/new-boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-special-announced/|title=New Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Anime Special Announced|date=13 June 2017|accessdate=20 March 2018|website=Comic Book|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170918055407/http://comicbook.com/anime/2017/06/13/new-boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-special-announced/|archivedate=18 September 2017|df=}}</ref>

The television anime series, supervised by series creator Ukyō Kodachi, is co-directed by [[Noriyuki Abe]] and Hiroyuki Yamashita, with series composition by [[Makoto Uezu]], animation produced by [[Pierrot (company)|Pierrot]], character designs by [[Tetsuya Nishio]] and Hirofumi Suzuki, and music co-composed by [[Yasuharu Takanashi]] and YAIBA. The series premiered on [[TV Tokyo]] on 5 April 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-02-23/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-reveals-more-cast-staff/.112598|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Anime Reveals More Cast, Staff|date=23 February 2017|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=23 February 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170701042418/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-02-23/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-reveals-more-cast-staff/.112598|archivedate=1 July 2017|df=}}</ref> Viz Media has licensed the series in North America.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-23/viz-media-licenses-boruto-tv-anime-plans-simulcast/.113823|title=Viz Media Licenses Boruto TV Anime, Plans Simulcast (Updated)|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323232746/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-23/viz-media-licenses-boruto-tv-anime-plans-simulcast/.113823|archivedate=23 March 2017|df=}}</ref> In promoting the anime, [[Crunchyroll]] started sharing free segments of the series in early 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2018/02/03/team-7-combination-attack-in-the-latest-boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-clip/|title=Team 7 Combination Attack In The Latest ‘Boruto: Naruto Next Generations’ Anime Clip|work=The Fandom Post|date=3 February 2018|accessdate=19 March 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417222203/https://www.fandompost.com/2018/02/03/team-7-combination-attack-in-the-latest-boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-clip/|archivedate=17 April 2018|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2018/01/11/orochimaru-vs-log-in-the-latest-boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-clip/|title=Orochimaru vs Log In The Latest ‘Boruto: Naruto Next Generations’ Anime Clip|work=The Fandom Post|date=11 January 2018|accessdate=19 March 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618145523/https://www.fandompost.com/2018/01/11/orochimaru-vs-log-in-the-latest-boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-clip/|archivedate=18 June 2018|deadurl=no}}</ref> The episodes are being collected in DVD boxes in Japan, starting with the first fifteen episodes on 1 November 2017.<ref name="neowing.co.jp">{{Cite web |url=http://www.neowing.co.jp/product/ANZB-14505 |title=Boruto-ボルト- Naruto Next Generations DVD-Box 2 [完全生産限定版] |website=Neowing |language=Japanese |date=8 November 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20171202205030/http://www.neowing.co.jp/product/ANZB-14505 |archivedate=2 December 2017 |df= }}</ref><ref name="neowing.co.jp"/> A CD soundtrack titled ''Boruto Naruto Next Generations Original Soundtrack 1'' was released on 28 June 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/product/SVWC-70274|title=Boruto Naruto Next Generations Original Soundtrack 1|website=Neowing|accessdate=20 March 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927155842/http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/product/SVWC-70274|archivedate=27 September 2017|df=}}</ref> The second soundtrack was released on 7 November 2018<ref>{{cite magazine |title= [[Weekly Shōnen Jump]] |publisher= [[Shueisha]] |date= August 2018 |issue= 2470}}</ref>

On 21 July 2018, it was announced at [[Comic-Con International: San Diego]] that the series will premiere on [[Adult Swim]]'s [[Toonami]] starting on 29 September.<ref>{{cite web |title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Anime to Premiere on Toonami on September 29 |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-07-22/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-to-premiere-on-toonami-on-september-29/.134564 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=July 22, 2018}}</ref>

===Other media===
A series of [[light novels]] written by Kō Shigenobu (novels 1-3 and 5) and Miwa Kiyomune (novel 4), with illustrations by Mikio Ikemoto, based on the anime have also been produced. The first one, titled {{nihongo|''The New Konoha Ninja Flying in the Blue Sky!''|青天を翔る新たな木の葉たち!|Seiten o Kakeru Aratana Konoha-tachi!}}, was released on 2 May 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_01.html|title=BORUTO -ボルト- -NARUTO NEXT GENERATIONS- NOVEL 1|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=18 August 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818144328/http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_01.html|archivedate=18 August 2018|df=}}</ref> A second one was released on 4 July 2017, under the title {{nihongo|''A Call From the Shadows!''| 影からの呼び声!|Kage Kara no Yobigoe!}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_02.html|title=BORUTO -ボルト- -NARUTO NEXT GENERATIONS- NOVEL 2|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=18 August 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818144552/http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_02.html|archivedate=18 August 2018|df=}}</ref> The third novel, {{nihongo|''Those Who Illuminate the Night of Shinobi!''|忍の夜を照らす者!|Shinobi no Yoru O Terasu Mono!}}, was released on 4 September 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_03.html|title=BORUTO -ボルト- -NARUTO NEXT GENERATIONS- NOVEL 3|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=18 August 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818144838/http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_03.html|archivedate=18 August 2018|df=}}</ref> The fourth novel, {{nihongo|''School Trip Bloodwind Records!''|修学旅行血風録!|Shūgakuryokō ketsu pū roku!}}, was released on 2 November 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_04.html|title=BORUTO -ボルト- -NARUTO NEXT GENERATIONS- NOVEL 4|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=22 August 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180822200404/http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_04.html|archivedate=22 August 2018|df=}}</ref> The fifth novel, {{nihongo|''The Last Day at the Ninja Academy!''|忍者学校最後の日!|Ninja akademī saigo no hi!}}, was released on 4 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_05.html|title=BORUTO -ボルト- -NARUTO NEXT GENERATIONS- NOVEL 5|publisher=[[Shueisha]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=22 August 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180822200738/http://j-books.shueisha.co.jp/books/boruto_05.html|archivedate=22 August 2018|df=}}</ref>

The upcoming [[Naruto#Video games|video game]] ''Naruto to Boruto: Shinobi Striker'' (2018) is aimed to contain characters from both the ''Boruto'' and ''Naruto'' series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guiltybit.com/entrevista-a-noriaki-niiko-productor-de-naruto-to-boruto-shinobi-striker/|website=GuiltyBit|language=Spanish|title=Entrevista a Noriaki Niiko, Productor de Naruto to Boruto: Shinobi Striker|date=25 August 2017|accessdate=11 April 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417222204/https://www.guiltybit.com/entrevista-a-noriaki-niiko-productor-de-naruto-to-boruto-shinobi-striker/|archivedate=17 April 2018|df=}}</ref> In August 2018, another ''Boruto'' game was announced for PC. Titled ''Naruto x Boruto Borutical Generations'', will be free to play, with options to purchase in-game items. The game will be available through the Yahoo! Game service.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-08/naruto-x-boruto-borutical-generations-pc-browser-game-revealed/.134801|title=Naruto x Boruto Borutical Generations PC Browser Game Revealed|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=August 10, 2018}}</ref>

==Reception==
===Manga===
The manga has been generally well-received in Japan; the compilations appeared as top sellers multiple times. In its release week, the first manga volume sold 183,413 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-02/japanese-comic-ranking-may-22-28/.116971|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, May 22–28|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=5 July 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170707190220/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-02/japanese-comic-ranking-may-22-28/.116971|archivedate=7 July 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-21/japanese-comic-ranking-december-12-18/.110212|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, December 12–18|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=5 July 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170621211815/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-12-21/japanese-comic-ranking-december-12-18/.110212|archivedate=21 June 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-10/japanese-comic-ranking-august-1-7/.105241|title=Japanese Comic Ranking, August 1–7|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=5 July 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702091435/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-10/japanese-comic-ranking-august-1-7/.105241|archivedate=2 July 2017|df=}}</ref> The series has one million copies in print {{as of|2017|January|lc=y}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-01-26/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-features-original-story/.111500|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Anime Features Original Story|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170608044519/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-01-26/boruto-naruto-next-generations-anime-features-original-story/.111500|archivedate=8 June 2017|df=}}</ref> Between 2017 and 2018, it became the 8th best-selling manga from Shueisha.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-04-06/manga-with-biggest-1st-printings-from-kodansha-shogakukan-shueisha-2017-2018/.130071|title=Manga With Biggest 1st Printings from Kodansha, Shogakukan, Shueisha: 2017-2018|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=6 April 2018|accessdate=6 May 2018}}</ref> The manga's first volume also sold well in North America,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://icv2.com/articles/markets/view/37458/top-300-graphic-novels-actual-april-2017|title=Top 300 Graphic Novels Actual--April 2017|website=[[ICv2]]|accessdate=9 July 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170720164208/https://icv2.com/articles/markets/view/37458/top-300-graphic-novels-actual-april-2017|archivedate=20 July 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://icv2.com/articles/markets/view/39359/top-1000-graphic-novels-2017-part-1|title=Top 1000 Graphic Novels--2017, Part 1|website=[[ICv2]]|accessdate=27 January 2017}}</ref> while the series became the sixth-best-selling serialised manga in 2017 according to ''[[ICv2]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-03-03/icv2-releases-list-of-top-10-manga-franchises-in-fall-2017/.128509|title=ICv2 Releases List of Top 10 Manga Franchises in Fall 2017|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=3 March 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180303225754/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-03-03/icv2-releases-list-of-top-10-manga-franchises-in-fall-2017/.128509|archivedate=3 March 2018|df=}}</ref>

Rebecca Silverman of ''[[Anime News Network]]'' (''ANN'') said ''Boruto'' appealed to her despite never having gotten into the ''Naruto'' manga. She praised how the writers dealt with Boruto's angst without it coming across as "teen whining" and the way Sasuke decides to train him.<ref name=ANN2>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2017-05-30/the-spring-2017-manga-guide/boruto-vol-1/.116744|title=The Spring 2017 Manga Guide Boruto Vol. 1|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170701034504/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2017-05-30/the-spring-2017-manga-guide/boruto-vol-1/.116744|archivedate=1 July 2017|df=}}</ref> Amy McNulty of ''ANN'' regarded the manga as appealing to fans of the original ''Naruto'' series, adding that while Mitsuki has a small role in the story, his side-story helps to expand his origins.<ref name=ANN2/> Nik Freeman of the same website criticised Boruto's lack of development in comparison with his introduction in ''Naruto''{{'}}s finale; Freeman also said there are differences between the reasons both the young Naruto and Boruto vandalised their village. Nevertheless, Freeman liked Mitsuki's backstory as he did not feel it retold older stories.<ref name=ANN2/> Reviewing the first chapter online, Chris Beveridge of ''The Fandom Post'' was more negative, complaining about the sharp focus on Naruto and Boruto's poor relationship and the retelling of elements from ''Boruto: Naruto the Movie''; Beveridge also criticised the adaptation of Kishimoto's artwork, but he praised the relationship between Naruto and Sasuke as well as the foreshadowing of a fight involving an older Boruto.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fandompost.com/2016/05/10/boruto-chapter-1-manga-review/|title=Boruto Chapter #1 Manga Review|work=The Fandom Post|date=10 May 2016|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170701055507/http://www.fandompost.com/2016/05/10/boruto-chapter-1-manga-review/|archivedate=1 July 2017|df=}}</ref>

Melina Dargis of the same website reviewed the first volume; she looked forward to the development of the characters despite having already watched the ''Boruto'' movie; she was also pleased by Mitsuki's role in his own side-story.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2017/05/19/boruto-vol-01-manga-review/|title=Boruto Vol. #01 Manga Review|work=The Fandom Post|date=19 May 2017|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820193209/http://www.fandompost.com/2017/05/19/boruto-vol-01-manga-review/|archivedate=20 August 2017|df=}}</ref> Leroy Douresseaux of ''Comic Book Bin'' recommended the series to ''Naruto'' fans, explaining how the new authors managed to use the first volume to establish the protagonists' personalities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/boruto001.html|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Volume 1 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|date=3 April 2017|accessdate=3 April 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420014452/http://www.comicbookbin.com/boruto001.html|archivedate=20 April 2017|df=}}</ref> Dargis was impressed by the apparent message of the series, which she found was trying to connect to modern audiences with themes such as parental issues and the use of technology, in contrast to ''Naruto''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fandompost.com/2017/10/16/boruto-vol-02-manga-review/|title=Boruto Vol. #02 Manga Review|work=The Fandom Post|date=16 October 2016|accessdate=18 October 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417222203/https://www.fandompost.com/2017/10/16/boruto-vol-02-manga-review/|archivedate=17 April 2018|df=}}</ref> Douresseaux liked that Boruto's character development had already started by the second volume of the series because it helped readers appreciate him more.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comicbookbin.com/boruto002.html|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Volume 2 manga review|website=Comic Book Bin|date=24 September 2017|accessdate=20 October 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417222203/http://www.comicbookbin.com/boruto002.html|archivedate=17 April 2018|df=}}</ref>

===Anime===
The anime was popular with Japanese readers of ''Charapedia'', who voted it the ninth best anime show of Spring 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://otakuusamagazine.com/LatestNews/News1/Japanese-Fans-Choose-the-Spring-2017-Anime-Worth-W-8955.aspx|title=Japanese Fans Choose the Spring 2017 Anime Worth Watching|website=[[Otaku USA]]|date=7 May 2017|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170612041808/http://otakuusamagazine.com/LatestNews/News1/Japanese-Fans-Choose-the-Spring-2017-Anime-Worth-W-8955.aspx|archivedate=12 June 2017|df=}}</ref> ''[[IGN]]'' writer Sam Stewart commended the focus on the new generation of ninjas as well as the differences between them and the previous generation. He praised the return of other characters like [[List of Naruto characters#Toneri Ōtsutsuki|Toneri Otsutsuki]] and enjoyed the eye techniques.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/05/25/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-8-the-dreams-revelation-review|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episode 8: "The Dream's Revelation" Review|work=[[IGN]]|date=25 May 2017|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170701060640/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/05/25/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-8-the-dreams-revelation-review|archivedate=1 July 2017|df=}}</ref> Stewart applauded the characterisation of both Shikadai and [[List of Naruto characters#Metal Lee|Metal Lee]], calling their relationship as well as accidental fight interesting to watch and saying ''Boruto: Naruto Next Generations'' improves with each episode.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/04/20/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-3-metal-lee-goes-wild-review|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episode 3: "Metal Lee Goes Wild!"|work=[[IGN]]|date=20 April 2017|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170530210420/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/04/20/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-3-metal-lee-goes-wild-review|archivedate=30 May 2017|df=}}</ref> Crunchyroll Brand Manager Victoria Holden joined ''IGN''{{'s}} Miranda Sanchez to discuss whether ''Next Generations'' could live up to the success of the old series while still reviewing previous episodes of the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/05/25/can-boruto-live-up-to-narutos-legacy|title=Can Boruto Live up to Naruto's Legacy?|work=[[IGN]]|date=25 May 2017|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531212344/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/05/25/can-boruto-live-up-to-narutos-legacy|archivedate=31 May 2017|df=}}</ref> According to TV Tokyo, sales and gross profits of ''Boruto'' have been highly positive during 2018 taking the top 5 spot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.txhd.co.jp/pdf/180518_kessan.pdf|title=TV Tokyo HD|publisher=TV Tokyo|accessdate=October 19, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref>

In a more comical article, ''[[Geek.com]]'' writer Tim Tomas compared ''Boruto'' with the series ''[[The Legend of Korra]]'', since both were different from their predecessors despite sharing themes with them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geek.com/culture/what-to-expect-from-viz-media-for-the-next-3000-years-1673964/|title=What To Expect From Viz Media For the Next 3000 Years|website=[[Geek.com]]|date=10 October 2016|accessdate=1 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107112130/http://www.geek.com/culture/what-to-expect-from-viz-media-for-the-next-3000-years-1673964/|archivedate=7 November 2016|df=}}</ref> Sarah Nelkin considered ''Boruto'' as a more lighthearted version of the ''Naruto'' series, but Amy McNulty praised its 13th episode for the focus on a subplot that had been developing since the first episode because its revelations made the series darker.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.anime-now.com/entry/2017/05/16/230044 |title=Boruto Is Basically What Naruto Would’ve Looked Like if the World Had Been at Peace |last=Nelkin |first=Sarah |date=16 May 2017 |website=Anime Now |accessdate=18 May 2017 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170612163429/http://www.anime-now.com/entry/2017/05/16/230044 |archivedate=12 June 2017 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/boruto-naruto-next-generations/episode-13/.118147 |title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episode 13 |last=McNulty |first=Amy |date=28 June 2017 |work=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=28 June 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630210717/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/boruto-naruto-next-generations/episode-13/.118147 |archivedate=30 June 2017 |df= }}</ref> Stewart agreed with McNulty, commenting that the developers reached the climax of the anime's first story arc. The villain's characterisation also impressed the reviewer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/06/29/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-13-the-demon-beast-appears-review|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episode 13: "The Demon Beast Appears!" Review|work=[[IGN]]|date=29 June 2017|accessdate=4 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702054040/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/06/29/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-13-the-demon-beast-appears-review|archivedate=2 July 2017|df=}}</ref> Allega Frank of ''Polygon'' mentioned that during the start of both the manga and the anime, multiple fans were worried due to a [[flashforward]] in which an older Boruto is facing an enemy named Kawaki who implies Naruto might be dead; his fate left them concerned.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2017/4/6/15208858/is-naruto-dead-in-boruto|title=Boruto premiere leaves fans nervous about Naruto’s fate|last=Frank|first=Allega|date=6 April 2017|website=Polygon|accessdate=4 July 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/20170408180836/http://www.polygon.com/2017/4/6/15208858/is-naruto-dead-in-boruto|archivedate=8 April 2017|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> The series ranked 80 in [[Tokyo Anime Award|Tokyo Anime Award Festival]] in the Best 100 TV Anime 2017 category.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://best100.animefestival.jp/finish.html|title= みんなが選ぶベスト100{{sic|nolink=y|Animes}} of 2017|publisher=[[Tokyo Anime Award]]|accessdate=15 March 2018|deadurl= no|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20171226234658/https://best100.animefestival.jp/finish.html|archivedate= 26 December 2017|df= }}</ref>

Critics also commented on Boruto's characterisation in the anime. Beveridge applauded the series' first episode, saying he felt Boruto's portrayal was superior to the one from the manga, while other writers enjoyed his heroic traits that send more positive messages to the viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fandompost.com/2017/04/05/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-01-anime-review/|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episode #02 Anime Review|work=The Fandom Post|date=5 April 2017|accessdate=2 June 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170701060415/http://www.fandompost.com/2017/04/05/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-01-anime-review/|archivedate=1 July 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/boruto-naruto-next-generations/episodes-31-32/.123784|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episodes 31-32|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=8 November 2017|accessdate=4 February 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205072430/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/boruto-naruto-next-generations/episodes-31-32/.123784|archivedate=5 February 2018|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://manga.tokyo/interview/an-interview-with-chihiro-ikki-the-voice-of-denki-kaminarimon-from-boruto-naruto-next-generations/2/|title=An Interview With Chihiro Ikki, The Voice of Denki Kaminarimon from Boruto: Naruto Next Generations|website=Manga Tokyo|last=Kouchi |first=Kanako|date=January 2018|accessdate=15 March 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316023836/https://manga.tokyo/interview/an-interview-with-chihiro-ikki-the-voice-of-denki-kaminarimon-from-boruto-naruto-next-generations/2/|archivedate=16 March 2018|df=}}</ref> Reviewers praised that the returning character Sasuke Uchiha had become more caring toward his daughter, Sarada, the female protagonist of the series, and they felt this highly developed the two characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/08/24/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-21-sasuke-and-sarada-review|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episode 21: "Sasuke and Sarada" Review|work=[[IGN]]|date=24 August 2017|accessdate=30 August 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831045904/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/08/24/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-21-sasuke-and-sarada-review|archivedate=31 August 2017|last=Stewart |first=Sam}}</ref> Critics felt this further helped to expand the connection between the Uchiha family members — Sasuke, Sakura, and Sarada — due to how their bond is portrayed during the anime's second story arc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anime-now.com/entry/2017/09/06/230036|title=In Boruto, Sasuke Is a Jerk Who Loves His Daughter|website=Anime Now|date=6 September 2017|accessdate=6 September 2017|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906182539/http://www.anime-now.com/entry/2017/09/06/230036|archivedate=6 September 2017|last=Iikura |first=Ken}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anime-now.com/entry/2017/09/15/230004|title=Sasuke & Sakura’s Marriage Has a Balance That’s Hard to See|website=Anime Now|date=15 September 2017|accessdate=15 September 2017|last=Nelkin |first=Sarah|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170916010856/http://www.anime-now.com/entry/2017/09/15/230004|archivedate=16 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/09/08/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-23-bonds-come-in-all-shapes-review|title=Boruto: Naruto Next Generations Episode 23: "Bonds Come In All Shapes" Review|last=Stewart |first=Sam|work=[[IGN]]|date=8 September 2017|accessdate=8 September 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170908204431/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/09/08/boruto-naruto-next-generations-episode-23-bonds-come-in-all-shapes-review|archivedate=8 September 2017}}</ref>

==Controversy==
In March 2018, Chinese animator Chengxi Huang posted a video of Naruto and Hinata embracing each other naked. The image got disapproval from young fans as they considered it "gross". Huang's apology stated that the animation was simply practice, and that he wanted to portray the everyday life of a married couple but still deleted the video in response.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.otakuusamagazine.com/animator-apologizes-posting-adult-naruto-animation/|title=Animator Apologizes After Posting Adult Naruto Animation|publisher=Otaku Usa|date=January 10, 2018|accessdate=September 11, 2018}}</ref>

