[[File:Mabel Bardine 001.jpg|thumb|Bardine in 1909]] '''Mabel Bardine Myers Farnsworth''' (October 25, 1878 - October 20, 1948), was an American vaudeville performer and Hollywood actress. In 1908 she was accused of plagiarizing the sketch, The Chorus Lady, from [[Rose Stahl]].<ref name=rose>{{cite news |author= |agency= |title=Mabel Berdine Coming Over |url=http://footlightnotes.tumblr.com/post/74687510203/mabel-bardine-1878-1948-american-vaudeville |newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=March 6, 1908 |accessdate=2015-06-05 }}</ref> She was a leading woman in [[Essanay Studios]] and [[Fox Film]].<ref name=win/>
==Biography== She was born as '''Mabel Bardine Myers''' on October 25, 1878 in [[Colorado]].
In 1908 she was accused of plagiarizing the sketch, The Chorus Lady, from [[Rose Stahl]].<ref name=rose/>
She died on October 20, 1948 in [[Los Angeles, California]]. She was buried in [[Forest Lawn Memorial Park (Glendale)|Forest Lawn Memorial Park]] in [[Glendale, California]].
